abstract: Members of the National Rifle Association, a protester and the mayor offered their thoughts on the N.R.A.’s 147th annual meeting.
snippet: Members of the National Rifle Association, a protester and the mayor offered their thoughts on the N.R.A.’s 147th annual meeting.
lead_paragraph: DALLAS — In a carpeted sea of guns — and knives and holsters and bullet-splat earrings — Charlie Harwood stopped in his tracks as the president’s son brushed past him at the 147th annual meeting of the National Rifle Association.
